OL,4,CMake Universal Credit top-up permanent
OL,5,C- Tory MPs
OL,6, Two Conservative MPs have written to
OL,7, Boris Johnson, urging him not to press
OL,8, on with plans to cut Universal Credit
OL,9, payments from October.
OL,11,FPeter Aldous and John Stevenson said
OL,12,Fthe #20-per-week increase, brought in
OL,13,Fas a response to the pandemic, should
OL,14,Fbe made permanent.
OL,16,FThe letter comes amid warnings from two
OL,17,Fcharities that cutting the uplift will
OL,18,Fpush millions of families into debt.
OL,20,FBut ministers have said the increase
OL,21,Fwas only ever a temporary measure.
